"63_cocoaui_stub.mst — CG1 placeholder for the conditional Cocoa GUI world
 layer (docs/cocoa_gui_design.md §12.3, sprint_cocoa_gui.md CG1). Loaded ONLY
 via `frontend::world::load_list(vm, world/cocoaui.list)`, NEVER from
 world/world.list — so the CLI, the WKWebView GUI, and the base test suite
 carry none of it. Its whole job in CG1 is to prove the extra layer compiles
 and runs on top of an already-booted base world (a fresh class that is absent
 from the base world, present only after load_list). The real CocoaUI /
 view-wrapper classes arrive in CG2+ (files 64+)."
"I am a tiny marker class for the optional native-GUI world layer, which
 loads on top of an already-booted base world. I exist to prove that layer
 compiles and runs: `ping` answers a Symbol a headless check can verify.
 I have no other behavior."
Object subclass: CocoaUIStub [
    "A trivial marker from the conditional layer. `ping` answers a Symbol so a
     headless gate can prove not just that the class resolves but that a method
     of it actually runs (an oop from the extra layer, printString-checkable)."
    CocoaUIStub class >> ping [ ^#cocoaUiStubReady ]
]
